pageContext.claim: “I didn't deal with Russia. I had nothing to do with Russia with respect to my race. I won that race rather easily.”
pageContext.analysis: Trump narrowly won the Electoral College, as a swing of less than 50,000 votes would have flipped three states and cost him the election. He is one of the few elected presidents to have lost the popular vote. During the campaign, Trump conducted negotiations with Russians about building a Trump tower in Moscow.
